"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#070707] p-5 mb-4","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider mb-4","children":"Prompt 1 — Demand forecast"}],["$","pre",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[12px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed whitespace-pre-wrap","children":"You are a restaurant operations analyst. Below is 12 weeks\nof daily cover counts and revenue from our POS system.\n\nPOS DATA (CSV):\n[PASTE CSV HERE]\n\nUPCOMING EVENTS NEXT WEEK:\n[PASTE NOTES HERE — e.g. \"Saturday: home game at nearby stadium\"]\n\nYour task:\n1. Identify the day-of-week pattern for covers over the\n   last 12 weeks (Mon-Sun averages, with range).\n2. Factor in any upcoming events that might affect demand.\n3. For each day of the coming week (Monday [DATE] through\n   Sunday [DATE]), forecast: expected covers (low / mid / high),\n   and recommended front-of-house staff count for lunch\n   and dinner shifts.\n4. Flag any days with unusually high uncertainty.\n5. Format as a clean table I can use to build a schedule."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#070707] p-5","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550] uppercase tracking-wider mb-4","children":"Prompt 2 — Schedule draft"}],["$","pre",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[12px] text-[#9a9590] leading-relaxed whitespace-pre-wrap","children":"Here is staff availability for next week and the demand\nforecast you just generated.\n\nSTAFF AVAILABILITY:\n[PASTE AVAILABILITY FROM GOOGLE SHEET OR WHATSAPP POLL]\n\nDEMAND FORECAST:\n[PASTE OUTPUT FROM PROMPT 1]\n\nSTAFFING RULES:\n- Lunch shift: 11am–3pm. Dinner shift: 4pm–10pm.\n- Minimum 1 server per 15 covers expected.\n- Always schedule 1 senior server on Friday + Saturday dinner.\n- Max 2 doubles per employee per week.\n\nDraft a schedule for the week. For each shift, list:\nwhich staff member is assigned, their role, and total hours.\nFlag any coverage gaps. Output as a plain text table."}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[12px] text-[#5a5550] mt-3 font-mono","children":"Adapt the staffing rules to your own ratios and constraints."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-14","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#c9a84c] mb-5","children":"Results — 60 Days In"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4","children":[["$","div","Labor cost as % of revenue",{"className":"border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d] p-4 flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center gap-3","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex-1","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#f0ede8] mb-2","children":"Labor cost as % of revenue"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550]","children":"30.4%"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-[#3a3530]","children":"→"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#9a9590]","children":"24.9%"}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex-shrink-0","children":["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[14px] text-[#c9a84c]","children":"−18%"}]}]]}],["$","div","Monthly labor savings",{"className":"border border-[#1e1e1e] bg-[#0d0d0d] p-4 flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center gap-3","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex-1","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-[13px] text-[#f0ede8] mb-2","children":"Monthly labor savings"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#5a5550]","children":"—"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-[#3a3530]","children":"→"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[11px] text-[#9a9590]","children":"$$3,400/mo"}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex-shrink-0","children":["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[14px] text-[#c9a84c]","children":"+$40,800/yr"}]}]]}],["$","div